: false, "params": [{"name": "d", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Inflate a flattened dictionary back into a nested dictionary.\n\nNested keys are indexed with a dot. For example,\n\nd = {\n    'a': 1,\n    'b.c': 2,\n    'b.d': 3,\n    'b.blah.foo': 67,\n    'b.blah.bar': 'no',\n    'e': 'lol'\n}\n\nbecomes\n\n{\n    'a': 1,\n    'b': {\n        'c': 2,\n        'd': 3,\n        'blah': {\n            'foo': 67,\n            'bar': 'no'\n        }\n    },\n    'e': 'lol'\n}", "%%"]}, {"name": "sorcerun.incense_utils.exps_to_xarray", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "exps", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exclude_keys", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert a list of incense experiments to two xarrays.\n\n```\nparam exps\n\ninput list of experiments\n\nparam exclude_keys\n\nconfig keys to exclude\n```\n\nReturns: tuple (exps_arr, metrics_arr)\nBoth are xarrays.\n\nexps_arr has dims given by the union of squished config keys over all experiments.\nThe corresponding coords are also the union over all possible values of the\ncorresponding config key. The value of each entry is the incense Experiment object.\n\nmetrics_arr is the same as exps_arr, with two additional dims: \"metric\" and \"step\".\nThe value of each entry is now the value of the metric at step \"step\" for each\nexperiment.\n", "%%"]}, {"name": "sorcerun.incense_utils.print_file_size", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sorcerun.incense_utils.process_and_save_grid_to_netcdf", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "gid", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "file_root", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sorcerun.incense_utils.xarray_to_csv", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "da", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "csv_filename", "type